{"content_type":"tech","visual_kind":"workflow_map","title":"Chain of Responsibility","subtitle":"Request flows through handlers — each can handle or pass","eyebrow":"Behavioral Pattern","panels":[{"heading":"Pipeline Mode","tag":"Every handler runs","bullets":["Auth → RateLimit → Validate → Handler","Each step can reject (short-circuit)","HTTP middleware is classic CoR"]},{"heading":"Escalation Mode","tag":"First match wins","bullets":["Manager → Director → VP","Pass until someone can handle","Approval chain, error recovery"]},{"heading":"vs Decorator","tag":"Distinction","bullets":["Decorator: always delegates, adds behavior","CoR: handler can STOP the chain"]},{"heading":"Key Trap","tag":"Warning","bullets":["Unclear stop/pass semantics","Chain order not tested","Handlers mutate request without contract"]}],"footer":"CoR = handlers can stop or pass. If every wrapper always delegates, that's Decorator.","output_path":"assets/design-pattern/images/cor-overview.png"}
